The paper deals with distributed computing and algorithms for Principal Component Analysis (PCA) in a distributed setting. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computational efficiency and communication cost of the algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions the use of PCA for clustering, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
